Privacy Policy —  Party Games

Last updated: July 1, 2026

Overview

 Party Games ("the App") is a local party game application developed by Falcon (_falcon). This privacy policy explains how the App handles your information.

The short version: we collect nothing. The App works entirely on your device.


Information We Collect

 Party Games does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal information whatsoever.

Specifically:


We do not collect your name, email address, or any identifying information
We do not collect device identifiers or advertising IDs
We do not use analytics or crash reporting services
We do not use third-party SDKs that collect data
We do not require an account or login of any kind
We do not access your camera, microphone, contacts, or location



Data Stored on Your Device

The App stores a small amount of data locally on your device only:


Player names you enter (saved so you don't have to retype them next session)
Your last-used game category selections


This data never leaves your device and is not accessible to us or any third party. You can clear it at any time by uninstalling the App.


Internet Access

 Party Games does not require an internet connection to play. The App may request network access solely as a technical requirement of the underlying React Native framework — no data is actually transmitted.


Children's Privacy

The App is suitable for all ages. Because we collect no personal information from any users, there are no special considerations for users under the age of 13 (COPPA) or under the age of 16 (GDPR).


Changes to This Policy

If we ever update this privacy policy, we will update the "Last updated" date above. Given the nature of this App (fully offline, no data collection), we do not anticipate any meaningful changes.


